article.headline: Yale 82, Harvard 74
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Sam Kaplan led six Yale players in double figures and the Bulldogs held off a late rally to defeat Harvard 82-74 on Friday. Yale (10-8, 2-1) led 72-57 with 3:15 left, but Harvard (10-6, 2-1) took advantage of three consecutive turnovers to pull within 10 points with 2:37 left. Harvard would cut the lead to six with 8.1 seconds left on a three-pointer from the corner by Zach Martin. But Yale freshman point guard Chris Andrews made two free throws with 7.4 seconds left to seal the win. Andrews scored a career-high 10 points, all from the free-throw line. Yale sophomore twin forwards Caleb and Nick Holmes scored 13 and 11, respectively. Caleb Holmes added six assists and six rebounds. Sophomore point guard Eric Flato had 12 points and senior center Dominick Martin had 10. Junior guard Jim Goffredo led Harvard with 21 points, while junior center Brian Cusworth added 16 and senior forward Matt Stehle had 13 points. Cusworth and Stehle each had nine rebounds. Martin, Stehle and Cusworth all fouled out.
